pageContext.claim: “Our relationship with North Korea has been very good. We've really established a good relationship with Kim Jong Un. I have personally. There's no rocket testing. There's no missile testing.”
pageContext.analysis: North Korea is testing missiles, and Trump has yet to receive any meaningful concessions despite his repeated and public embraces of the dictator Kim Jong Un, which experts say have legitimized the regime on the world stage like never before while the U.S. has secured little in return.
